Do you have the PWM cables they came with? If so, you could try cutting off the single DuPont connector and replacing it with two pairs of CAN wires. You’ll need to pay attention to the pinout, but electrically both signals go to the same place.

That’s fine for the normal PWM wires. But crimping those JST connectors, especially with the jumpers so your bus doesn’t fail if the SPARK dies, isn’t so easy. You might do it if you’re in a pinch, but better to use the professionally-crimped ones from REV.

Let’s Go Wago! A pair of wire cutters/strippers + Wago - JST = hassle free CAN.
100% Wago in 2023. NO JST’s. Tons of hard hits 0 failures. NOTE: we do use ferrules on the CAN wires. A simple non scientific pull test using Wagos and bare wires vs Wago’s and ferrules will prove that the ferrules make a huge difference.
